  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "In GnuCash, a commodity is anything that can be traded or held as a unit of value — currencies, stocks, mutual funds, and even physical goods. Every [account](../../terms/account.md) in GnuCash is denominated in a commodity. Most accounts use a currency (USD, EUR), but investment accounts use securities as their commodity.",
